cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as dependency parsing, semantic role labeling, and named entity recognition. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training language models and producing contextual word representations. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing methods to improve crosslingual transfer. 

It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves training neural language models. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves improving the representation of text for various NLP tasks.
